@page
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Release Notes";
}
<p>What's new in the ePegboard web app at <a href="https://play.epegboard.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">play.epegboard.com</a>. The web app ships continuously - the highlights below cover the major themes.</p>

<h2 class="mt-4">🌐 Web app (play.epegboard.com)</h2>
<p class="text-muted"><em>Launched 2026-Q2. Ships continuously - this lists themes rather than individual versions.</em></p>

<ul class="fs-5">
    <li><strong>Web app launched</strong> - runs in any browser on any device. No install. Tablet or laptop-sized screens recommended for the best experience.</li>
    <li><strong>Picker improvements</strong> - the matchmaking algorithm has had significant work; the most common complaint we heard was higher-rated players paired with weak partners, and that's been the main driver.</li>
    <li><strong>Pick explanations</strong> - players see exactly why each game was picked.</li>
    <li><strong>Fairness statistics</strong> - mid-session visibility of wait-time fairness, partner / opponent variety.</li>
    <li><strong>Ratings graphs</strong> - per-player rating progression over time.</li>
    <li><strong>Attendance reports</strong> - built-in, helpful for member-retention conversations.</li>
    <li><strong>Multi-device access</strong> - multiple operators can hit the same session from different devices simultaneously.</li>
</ul>

<hr class="my-5" />

<p class="text-muted">Looking for the Windows desktop app? Its version history has moved to the <a asp-page="/DesktopReleaseNotes">desktop app release notes</a>. The desktop app continues to be supported, but most new functionality is now going into the web app.</p>
